SIMPLE: naturalized
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: naturalized
<hw>naturalized</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Acclimated to a
new environment; introduced from another region and persisting without
cultivation; -- of plants or animals not native to a location.</def>
<wns>[wns=1 & 3]</wns>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> domesticated, nonnative.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>planted randomly in soil so as to give an appearance
of wild growth; <as>as, drifts of <ex>naturalized</ex>
daffodils</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Naturally</ent>⟦br⟧
